# AkronWorld.umap

This file is a binary Unreal Engine 5 World Partition level.
It must be created inside the Unreal Editor — it cannot be generated from text.

## To create:

1. Open the project in Unreal Editor 5.5
2. File → New Level → Empty Open World (World Partition)
3. Save As: Content/Maps/AkronWorld.umap
4. Configure World Partition:
   - Grid size: 128 x 128
   - Cell size: ~500m
   - Runtime streaming: Distance-based
5. Add the `CruiseSprintGameMode` to World Settings
6. Add a PlayerStart actor
7. Save

This placeholder file can be deleted once the real .umap is created.
